race.description: Evergreen Turf Mncra Country Champs Qualifier Plate (C5)
race.comment: LUNAITE (14) is a promising mare resuming for Paul Snowden. Goes like a rocket fresh; scoring stylishly when resuming at Rosehill last campaign over this journey. Has been readied with a sharp trial and reunites with winning hoop. Will take some stitching. PONY SOPRANO (3) deserves his chance after returning with a bang here two weeks ago. Has built a handy record for himself and can take the next step. Favourable draw another tick. BODHI BOY (1) returns and is another that is a proven fresh performer. Two trials will have him forward but will need some from magic from Bullock out there. KAIHOKO (2) was a flashing light two weeks ago when flashing home behind PONY SOPRANO. Drawn better and is worth following up. Also can't knock the form of CALYPSO ROCKET (5).
